long_desc.thetext:
When using qooxdoo it's happen many time that i builded widget based on multiples component.
Most of the time the collaborators of my classes are located in namespace or one that is close to the current name space.

As  the time pass i had to had more and more time the same namespace in my class.
So i'm wondering if it would be easy to add a import class config key to support an import mechanism.

As an example
qx.Class.define("a.b.c.d.e.F",{
extend:qx.core.Object,
...
import:{localE,a.b.c.d.e},
members:{
fun:function(){
 var x = new this.imports("localeE").G();
}
}
});

I think the imported name space should be unmodifiable, this is why i dont porposed some accs like this:
new this.LocaleE.G()


Off course this will make refactoring more easy, if a namespace change we need to change it only one time per class
